Apple released infamous “1984”ad, advertising the new Macintosh computer. The ad revolutionized the industry and drew unprecedented attention to Apple despite only airing once publicly.

text.tspan: UK & China sign Hong Kong Treaty

g.text: UK and China sign agreement to revert Hong Kong to China in 20 years. This marks the ending of a UK ruled era in Hong Kong.
Amidst rising hostility towards his government practices and an economic downturn, Prime Minister Trudeau retires. His successor John Turner was sworn in the same day.
Canadian TV channels “TSN” and “MUCH” air for the first time within days of one another. Both Canadian channels became major players in the music/sports entertainment industry.
Supreme court of Canada determines the current ant-abortion law to be unconstitutional andrepeals it immedietly.
Succeeding the 1984 Sarajevo winter olympics, Calgary, Alberta hosted the Winter Olympic Games to over 1400 atheletes.
Military conflict due to a land dispute between historic rivals, Iran and Iraq, comes to an end.
The first ever internet worm was discovered. Created by a Cornell University student, it resulted in the first felony conviction of a cyber crime.
Tiger Woods at sixteen years old joins the PGA, the youngest in over thirty five years.
Montreal celebrates it’s 350th anniversary since it’s founding in 1642.
Mount Logan was measured finally by and expedition lead by the Royal Canadian Geographic Society. The height was confirmed using GPS.
Disney musical film ‘Aladdin’ was released, grossing the highest of all films in 1992
Claimed to be the first 64 bit system, Nintendo released the sucessor to the SNES to worldwide acclaim. It sold nearly 33 million units as of 2009.
Major League Soccer in North America has opening season. Despite initially performing poorly to draw in an audience, the league now draw more audience attendents then the NHL or NBA.
Dolly the sheep becomes first animal ever to be successfully cloned. Dolly lived for seven years and died of the same disease that killed the sheep that she was cloned from.
The tomb of the unknown soldier in Canada was constructed, and the remains of an unknown Canadian were brought back from Vimy Ridge.

g.text: Mark Zuckerberg releases social media website Facebook to the public. The website today has 1.86 billion daily users.
Dalai Lama visits Canada, drawing crowds of thousands to his talks and teachings.
Through the use of a “power-switching operation”, Vladamir Putin reassumed the role of Prime Minister.
Final performance of actor Heath Ledger, “The Dark Knight” releases to worldwide acclaim. The movie is considered one of the best Batman films of all time.
Despite immense controversy throughout the entire campaign Donald Trump is elected the next United States President
Smaller community Fort McMurray is effected by raging wildfire. The fire caused the relocation of thousands and resulted in almost 13 billion dollars in total costs.
Aztec calendar marked to end on December the 21st.
Queen Elizabeth II’s Diamon Jubilee occurs marking the Queens 60th anniversary on the throne. Canada dedicates a week to celebrations.
